Witcher Swords\par

\pard\sa160\sl259\slmult0\b0 Steel for men, when wielding a witchers sword made of steel (or other similar metals) and no other weapons, you gain +2 to damage rolls vs humanoids.\par
Silver for monsters, when wielding a witchers sword made of silver and no other weapons, you gain +2 to damage rolls vs all non-humanoid creatures.\par
A Witchers sword is a specialised tool, forged to the highest of standards and enchanted with magical runes, it requires a specialist smith to forge a Witchers blade. As such, the time needed to craft, and the cost to buy a Witchers blade are considerably higher than their standard counterparts. The length of time and cost are at the DMs discretion.\par
The magical runes inscribed onto a Witchers sword can be used to attach a magical effect to the weapon.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Witchers swords share the same stats as a standard Longsword.\par
Additionally, switching between one-handed and two-handed on a Witcher sword requires no action or bonus action. (Discuss with Jamie about raising damage at levels.)\b\par
